result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennifer E. Vis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver Schedule IV Drugs, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(i).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

case called at 10:15am. [MK]
Defendant Jennifer E. Vis in court with Attorney Jeffrey J De La Rosa.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
ADA Shock verifies victim rights compliance as to the intended referral read-in .

On Motion of the State, the Court strikes the park-location enhancer from the charging language. 

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of "  No Contest " entered on Count #2; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Ms. Vis guilty of Count #2, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #1, #3; further, the Court reads in an uncharged Jefferson Police Department referral for Theft with a date of violation of 6/8/14 (DA Case #2014JE1136) and thereafter bars further prosecution of this referral.

On Count # 2, the Court withholds sentence, and places Ms. Vis on Probation for 18 months, with conditions:
--to serve 29 days in the Jefferson County Jail, with work-release privileges for all purposes, to commence on 1/2/15 at 7:00pm.
---Ms. Vis is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in her system; non-compliance will result in loss of work-release privileges without further process.
--to undergo AODA assessment within sixty days of release from Jail, and to follow through with all recommended treatment
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, and counseling as required by the Agent
--no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--to take all prescription medications only as prescribed

--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as approved by the Agent, and except for incidental contact for employment or educational programming as approved by the Agent 
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon request
--to pay costs of $268 plus the $250 DNA surcharge plus a $25 drug testing fees plus the $75 controlled buy-fund reimbursment

case called at 1:10pm. 
Defendant Jennifer E. Vis is not in court.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.
ADA Teuber motions for the Court to issue a bench warrant. ADA Teuber provides the basis for this request, including that this was the date that Ms. Vis selected as being a workable date for her to appear, after she had contacted the DA's Office by telephone on June 20th to say that she could not appear on the the original June 24th court date.
ADA Teuber reports that Ms. Vis telephoned the DA's Office twice today: during the first telephone call she indicated that she cannot appear today because she is ill, and then she left a voicemail on her second call, asking to reschedule and advising she would not come today. 

The Court has read the Criminal Complaint; there is probable cause set forth in the Criminal Complaint.
ADA Teuber confirms that the Hawthorne Avenue, Janesville address was the address that Ms. Vis provided during to the DA's Office staff during the June 20th phone call.
The Court orders issuance of an arrest warrant- body only.
